Package: WarsawTraffic
Title: Simulator of the impact of traffic disruptions on the Warsaw public transit network
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    c(person("Adam", "Jaworski", email = "ap.jaworski3@student.uw.edu.pl", role = c("aut", "cre")),
      person("Natalia", "Namysłowska", email = "n.namyslowsk@student.uw.edu.pl", role = c("aut")))
Description: WarsawTraffic provides tools to simulate the real-time impact of
    traffic and infrastructure disruptions on the Warsaw public transit network.
    Users can fetch live GPS positions for buses and trams from the Warsaw Open
    Data API, drop a disruption pin on an interactive map, and instantly see
    which lines are affected based on spatial intersection with pre-processed
    GTFS route geometries. The package implements an R6 class hierarchy
    (Vehicle, Bus, Tram, TransitNetwork) to manage vehicle state, and exposes
    a Shiny dashboard for interactive exploration of disruption scenarios.
